doc.after: The Song dynasty 960 1279 AD was a culturally rich and sophisticated age for China There was blossoming of and advancements in the visual arts music literature and philosophy Officials of the ruling bureaucracy who underwent a strict and extensive examination process reached new heights of education in Chinese society while general Chinese culture was enhanced by widespread printing growing literacy and various arts
